reviews.comment: This was the hardest course I've taken so far at UBC. As an arts student, I felt out of my depth a lot of the time, but Dr. K made the whole experience worth it. Her exams are HARD - but I learned so much and would take this course again. The group project sucks tho. She is extremely accessible during office hours and on Piazza.

Do not take this prof. She doesn't tell you anything about what you're graded on before submission, she provides little to no resources for assignments, and the group project is quite useless and largely has nothing to do with computer science. This course is just a waste of time.

Professor K is a great lecturer and really nice but the quizzes and final were SO HARD. The class averages for the quizzes were all under 65% (one was 50%) before scaling which was needed due to such a low average. The old exams were nothing like the quizzes but if you grind really hard an A is possible (sorta) but this is not a GPA booster anymore

Dr. K was a fantastic professor with fun and engaging lectures. The quizzes were very difficult compared to what we learned in class. You need to pay attention in class and attend them, otherwise you'll be very confused.

Dr. Ola is funny and truly cares about her students! The downside of CPSC 100 was that our quizzes were too difficult and the grading criteria for our group project were constantly changing. However, Dr. Ola did end up scaling the quiz and would replace quiz marks with our final test mark if we did better on the final! So the course was fair!
Great prof. I actually had the motivation to attend the 9:30AM class just because she is that great of a professor. Very accessible outside of class and is always willing to help.
Dr. K is very knowledgable about data science and a great lecturer, but beware of DSCI 320. This course is A LOT of work.

she is pretty caring and her class is pretty fun but her quizzes are absolutely the hardest things. the practice questions have nothing to do with the difficulty level of the quizzes whatsoever. she is understanding and helpful but the quiz just make it hard to do well in the class
She's a very caring and knowledgable prof. The only issue I had was with the 3 "quizzes." throughout the term. Hard to study for.

Kemi Ola is THE BEST! It's very apparent that she cares for the students and tries to ensure everyone is learning at their best. She hosts frequent office hours and tries to work with students who are struggling to get them back up to speed. Her explanations are clear. She even made a public Spotify playlist for our section!

She is a sweet, lovely, and caring professor!
She's the type of person who answers every question with great care and attention. 
If you are struggling with the content, please go to office hours! She WILL HELP YOU.
She takes students' feedback seriously, and does as much as possible to help them succeed. 
AMAZING prof! wanna retake the course fr
Always try to make the class fun and not boring. Really care about her students, and good teaching style.

Great choice for CPSC110! Dr. K was extremely encouraging and gave clear explanations throughout the course. Although the course was challenging, Dr. K made lectures exciting and something I would look forward to.

She is one of the best professors! Her lectures are interesting and engaging; she always answers questions and explains concepts in a way that is easy to understand. Although CPSC 110 is a challenging course, she made the learning easy.

Although I didn't have Dr. K as my actual professor, I always watched her recorded lectures and went to her office hours because she is absolutely fantastic! Really cares about her students and explains challenging concepts super clearly and detailed. Highly recommend if you want to to learn from an amazing prof while also having fun!

Dr. K is a real educator, and is better than probably most of the profs in UBC. Lectures are very clear, takes the effort to answer questions, is respectful and friendly to students. A breath of fresh air.

Dr.K is the best professor I've had in this horrible school called UBC, her lectures are actually engaging, and she seems to actually care about making us improve and succeed in this course, despite it being fully online she does a better job than all the profs ive had for in person lectures. WOULD HIGHLY RECOMMEND SHE IS OP

Dr. K is such a cool prof and makes CPSC 110 a lot less daunting. 110 is a fast-paced course and ended up taking up most of my time compared to the other classes I had. It's easy to fall behind so make sure that you are on top of all your PSETS and understand them fully before the next class.

Dr. K has an amazing personality and makes 110 feel less daunting than it actually is. 110 is a fast-paced course and it's easy to fall behind, so make sure you always do you psets early and come to office hours if you have questions.

Prof. Ola was probably one of my favorite professors so far, very positive and caring. She was receptive to feedback and based her lectures around what the class struggled with the most, sometimes creating her own diagrams to help. This was my 2nd time taking the course, and I found the grading far more reasonable than the first time I took it.
Very enjoyable class. Felt tough but I thought grading was fair.

This isn't an easy course and the final does require a thorough understanding of the material. However, Kemi was a super enjoyable professor with a unique style of lecturing. She 's laid back and funny but still makes sure that the class is understanding the material. Would recommend, long as you can prepare for the final.

Dr. K was a caring prof, and I really liked how she tries to incorporate some life stories into her lectures, as well as playing some music before the class starts. I took this course as a science credit.

Dr. K was awesome period. She really cares about her students' mental health and wellbeing. The grading is really fair and unambiguous. Honestly one of my favorite profs this year. She's wholesome, sweet, and we have to protect her at all costs.

Dr. K was one of my favourite profs this term and she makes me more excited for my higher-level CPSC classes! I'm super grateful to have had her for my first comp sci experience as she made it all the better with her nerdy jokes much-needed breaks in the middle of lectures :)

I am not a fan of CPSC and took it as a pre requisite but Professor Kemi made this course SUPER enjoyable. I loved listening to the lectures and actually learned so much. Would definitely take another course with this professor.

Dr. Kemi is a fun and caring professor who makes class super interesting. She teaches in a way that is engaging yet effective. She listens to feedback and makes time to answer students' questions. Super chill and genuinely wants her students to succeed. Just make sure to keep up with the hw and practice material.

Kemi is one of the kindest professors out there! Although we had online learning, she never made it feel like we were missing out. We had a class spotify which she would play at the beginning of class. CPSC 110 can be a bit tough, but there's lots of practice material that I recommend doing!

Dr. Kemi is an amazing professor, she teaches 110 well and makes her lectures enjoyable with references to popular culture and livens up lectures by letting us make a spotify playlist to play at the start of class. Her office hours are also accessible and helpful, and it's clear she genuinely wants her students to succeed.
Nice prof, clearly explain all the knowledge. The material of this course is too easy tho.
Really nice prof, lecture is pretty organized, explain the knowledge very clearly.

Dr.K is one of the profs that makes me want to show up in their lectures. Spreading positive energy and encouraging students to do better. She cares about her students, really enjoyed talking to her. Solid choice.

I don't understand why there's so many bad reps. Dr. K is super energetic and enthusiastic during her lectures which helps me to focus. The course was hard and you'd fail if you can't keep up but she was good at explaining the concepts.

not exactly a lot of reading, but videos and time spent outside of class learning on edx. ola is really nice and even tho the course is heavy (if youre a first year), she is really nice and understanding. conveys in an enjoyable way and explains everything with openness to students with question and ensuring everyone understands.

Don't get me wrong. As a person Kemi Ola is a amazing. Her lectures are good as well. But her tests are something else. She expects you to dissect each lecture and read in between the lines. This course wasn't supposed to be programming heavy but programming questions were worth a lot of marks on the exams. The course needs to be restructured

She gave us a hard midterm (not representative of class material). I posted on a piazza thread saying I felt discouraged abt my mark. She wrote a long reply... which I cried while reading bc it was so rude. She basically said my feelings didn't make sense to her & I was being rude to the teaching team?? Clearly, she doesn't care abt mental health.
Kemi is the goat. Great energy and teaches very well. She is super engaging and helpful. My fav prof easily
You will regret taking any course from her. Honestly she just brags in class about how she was in the top of her year rather than teach anything actually related to the course
NEVER take a course with her. What was supposed to be a GPA booster course was made hard for no reason. She likes it when you fail

Personally, I loved Dr. K. She was so hilarious in lectures and went through powerpoints in a way that made it super engaging. This class has a lot of additional things to do, which can get annoying, but everything is graded fairly easily. So, its a matter of quantity of tasks, but still getting good grades. Enjoyed this course.
The class itself is pretty difficult. Kemi teaches it well, though. If you're gonna take this class try to keep on top of the lectures for sure. Also the last half of the class is pretty difficult.

Kemi was such a fun professor! She's literally the best. Fun and engaging lectures combined with exciting content from the course made for super enjoyable semester with her. You can tell she truly cares for her students and their learning. 10/10 would recommend.

DO NOT take a class with her. She does not teach! Her exams are extremely hard. We had a failing average for our first midterm. She is also not understanding and does not try to improve her lectures with student feedback. She is extremely unprofessional.

Dr.K was by far one of the WORST professors I have ever had. She spends all class joking around and talking about irrelevant stuff. Her tests are extremely hard and does not test you on what she teaches you in class. She does not provide ANY practice problems that are actually similar to her tests. Our midterm 1 average was 46%. AVOID HER!

I wish that the profs took more care and attention into the wording of exam questions. It's absolutely depressing when you understand your material inside out, but come exam time, the exam questions are so ambiguous that you have no clue what they are asking for. Fun but do you really learn anything..? hmmm...

lectures are fun as hell, she jokes around with you a lot, and she makes sure you understand the material. there is a lot of pre-class work and current tests are a lot of application rather than regurgitation, so make sure you understand the material.
Absolute beauty of a prof. Is able to make very complicated topics intuitive and easy to understand. Loved her lectures and fun-loving personality. Hopefully I see more of her thoughout my undergrad.

Kemi is a very good prof imo, she is very helpful in OH and I enjoyed her lectures, she is clear in her lectures and good-paced. The grading was fair though this courses content is not the easiest and assignment can take time

The course and the teaching team was a mess. During Covid-19 you would think she would care about students. Every exam we had was based on things not taught in class. Mandatory to show up to lectures but the lectures are useless as its not testable. Very disorganized. They do not take student feedback well either
She is a prof who is always happy and motivated to teach and help her students. The whole CPSC 110 course is a heave load but I don't think it's her fault.

She is very friendly and enthusiastic about CPSC. The teaching team makes it clear that students have to work hard to do well in the course. Participation and correct answers via clicker questions are for marks. Difficult course but very interesting nonetheless. They also give lots of opportunities to ask questions in office hours and in tutorials.

She's a really kind and caring professor. I thought her lectures were clear/organized. The only problem I had was that her writing can be a bit messy sometimes, but she'll clarify what she's writing if you ask her! She would always answer tons of student questions in class, which was nice because it cleared up confusion about the content right away

She was really nice outside of class and was genuine. However, her slides were quite unprofessional and kind of sloppy. She'll crack jokes in lectures which is always fun but the class was pretty disorganized.
Very disorganized. She should not be allowed to teach. I learn by myself. Will never go with her.
She was much better in CPSC110, but she was alright with 213 too. A little confusing and disorganized this term. She's still a decent prof though.

Her lectures are super fun and she really cares about the students' learning. For an introductory CPSC course, her class was amazingly enjoyable. If you are unsure whether you want to pursue CS or not, I would definitely recommend taking her classes and even talking to her about possible ways to get into the CS field. Excellent teacher!

She truly cares about the wellbeing of her students which is a refreshing change from other CPSC profs!! She is such a good and engaging lecturer and Im so glad I was in her section!! I love what she brings to the CPSC department. Regardless of what prof you get for CPSC 110 its really on you to watch the videos and master all the material!!

One of the most phenomenal profs I've ever had, and I have had some amazing profs. She's funny, demanding, engaging, and cares about her students. Her personality fills the lecture hall, and it's a pleasure to go to class. I looked forward to that class after a long day of lectures. Take her at all costs, you will not regret!!
Great, caring professor. Makes a conscious effort to memorize her students by name and has very lighthearted, funny, yet highly educational lectures.

her lectures are engaging and straightforward tests are straightforward would recommend you learn about computer science without it being coding heavy no coding experience needed group project is worth 15%

Her lecture style is easy to follow + she's always clear. She's always looking for ways to improve and genuinely cares for the content. Easy to pay attention and follow along. Group project isn't too bad + not worth that much. Actual project is worth 7.5% and the other 7.5% is peer evaluation + proposal. Course is a GPA booster. Must take with her!

I was online but I sneaked into a couple of her lectures. Ola is an amazing person. She explains the material really well and cares so much about the students. She tells great stories and makes the lectures really fun.

Great professor + genuinely took feedback to improve course. average was 81 course content isn't hard but if you're looking for more useful applications take CPSC110. online quizzes aren't hard b/c it's from the lecture notes + best 3/5 quizzes. group work - "15%" but more like 7.5% since you get marked on group feedback etc. would recommend her

This class teaches you so many useless things, and requires so much time. The online quizzes are super difficult, their is a ton of group work, and an excessive amount of homework. The readings are ridiculously long and she assigns a lot of them, and the tests are pretty strange and ambiguous... this class will have you pulling your hair out...
Dr. K has been my favourite prof my entire time at UBC. She really does truly care about her students and I really respect that.

This prof, the way she explains things: it's all just so logical and it makes so much sense. She understands her students very well and is truly caring. Sometimes I sit in class wondering if I can ever achieve such a high level of intelligence and academic aptitude in my lifetime. Easily the best prof I've ever had at this university.
really bad prof. skipped lectures because she was terrible at explaining. all i had to do was complete problem sets and got a 95

Such a phenomenal prof - definitely one of the best I've ever had, and I've had some GOOD profs. She is warm, demanding, funny, and explains things like no one else does. Coming to lecture wasn't a chore at all. Really hope she stays and teaches other courses. She's one of those profs you'll never forget.

Dr. Ola is the best prof i've had so far at UBC. She is so kind and approachable which really enhances students learning when they are struggling. She does an amazing job at talking with students and helping them out in office hours in addition to being a charismatic and engaging lecturer. I never felt bored in the 1.5 hour lectures, very special.
She's a great and caring prof, really cares about her students and loves teaching!

Great comp sci prof that made lectures very lighthearted and borderline fun. She even wrote a poem for us on the last class and she knows student names. However the course itself is very high workload especially for people without coding experience. Exams were fair and the course team is very caring and understanding of student struggles.
Truly the pinnacle of human evolution. Can't wait for her poetry she promised to do at the end of the semester.
Very nice prof, is always happy to discuss homework and concepts during office hours. The problem sets can be exceedingly difficult with a tight grading scheme, but those are graded by the TAs.

Lectures make the class deceivingly easy. There is a lab component which is also easy. This class was said to be a GPA booster. IT. IS. NOT. The midterm was so much harder than everything we had learned in class and had things on the test that weren't even covered in lecture. The labs and lecture do not prepare you for the exam.
